  "target_response": {
    "text": "On track in direction, early in distance. Your 7-day average HRV of 53 ms is about 2 ms above the 30-day mean of 51.2 ms, and that slow upward drift is exactly how real HRV progress looks. The distance is the honest part: the target is 60 ms, and closing a gap like that typically takes months of consistent sleep and aerobic base rather than weeks, with plenty of noisy dips along the way. So judge yourself on the monthly average only; single mornings — even a 54 ms one like today — are weather, not climate. Focus for the next few weeks: protect a consistent bedtime and keep most riding easy, since those two levers shift HRV more reliably than harder training does. Reassess when the 30-day mean itself crosses the mid-50s — that milestone is what makes the fall target live.",
